<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">A new record for the Greek flora.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
As currently understood, 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Aethionema" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aethionema saxatile" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="saxatile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Aethionema saxatile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) R.Br. is quite variable in Greece. It consists of four subspecies with a more or less distinct geographical distribution that deserve the rank of subspecies (
<bibRefCitation author="Andersson, I. A." journalOrPublisher="Willdenowia" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="3 - 42" refId="B7667741" refString="Andersson, I. A., Carlstroem, A., Franzen, R., Karlen, Th., Nybom, H., 1983. A revision of the Aethionema saxatile complex (Brassicaceae). Willdenowia 13: 3 - 42" title="A revision of the Aethionema saxatile complex (Brassicaceae)" volume="13" year="1983">Andersson et al. 1983</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kougioumoutzis, K." journalOrPublisher="Plant Biosystems" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="108 - 116" refId="B7668859" refString="Kougioumoutzis, K., Kalpoutzakis, E., Constantinidis, Th., 2017. Multivariate morphometric analysis and taxa delimitation in two narrow Greek endemics: Astragalus maniaticus and Aethionema saxatile subsp. corinthiacum. Plant Biosystems 151 (1): 108 - 116" title="Multivariate morphometric analysis and taxa delimitation in two narrow Greek endemics: Astragalus maniaticus and Aethionema saxatile subsp. corinthiacum" volume="151" year="2017">Kougioumoutzis et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Certain specimens from NW Greece resemble a fifth subspecies, subsp. 
<taxonomicName authority="saxatile" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Aethionema" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aethionema saxatile subsp. saxatile" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="saxatile" subSpecies="saxatile">Aethionema saxatile saxatile</taxonomicName>
, but statistical analyses of morphological characters showed that they cannot be placed with certainty under either subsp. 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Aethionema" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aethionema saxatile subsp. oreophilum" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="saxatile" subSpecies="oreophilum">Aethionema saxatile oreophilum</taxonomicName>
or subsp. 
<taxonomicName authority="saxatile" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Aethionema" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aethionema saxatile subsp. saxatile" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="saxatile" subSpecies="saxatile">Aethionema saxatile saxatile</taxonomicName>
. A related species, 
<taxonomicName genus="Ae." lsidName="Ae. rhodopaeum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="rhodopaeum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Ae. rhodopaeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
D.K. Pavlova (
<bibRefCitation author="Pavlova, D." journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="533 - 540" refId="B7669073" refString="Pavlova, D., 2007. A new species of Aethionema (Brassicaceae) from the Bulgarian flora. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 155: 533 - 540" title="A new species of Aethionema (Brassicaceae) from the Bulgarian flora" volume="155" year="2007">Pavlova 2007</bibRefCitation>
), so far considered endemic to Bulgaria, was treated as another subspecies of the 
<taxonomicName genus="Ae." lsidName="Ae. saxatile" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="saxatile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Ae. saxatile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kougioumoutzis, K." journalOrPublisher="Plant Biosystems" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="108 - 116" refId="B7668859" refString="Kougioumoutzis, K., Kalpoutzakis, E., Constantinidis, Th., 2017. Multivariate morphometric analysis and taxa delimitation in two narrow Greek endemics: Astragalus maniaticus and Aethionema saxatile subsp. corinthiacum. Plant Biosystems 151 (1): 108 - 116" title="Multivariate morphometric analysis and taxa delimitation in two narrow Greek endemics: Astragalus maniaticus and Aethionema saxatile subsp. corinthiacum" volume="151" year="2017">Kougioumoutzis et al. (2017)</bibRefCitation>
. It is a serpentine endemic with a local distribution to suitable geological substates of the Rodopi area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
The cited specimen, collected in Greece in 2019 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStartId="F7677592" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">12</figureCitation>
), has a combination of features that place it under 
<taxonomicName genus="Ae." lsidName="Ae. saxatile subsp. rhodopaeum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="subSpecies" species="saxatile" subSpecies="rhodopaeum">Ae. saxatile subsp. rhodopaeum</taxonomicName>
: a) short stems, usually less than 10 cm long; b) unilocular fruits present at a relatively high proportion (&gt;30-40% of total fruit number); c) lack of appendages on filaments; d) dark pink to pink-purplish petals and e) a particular preference for the rocky, serpentine habitats of the Kompsatos River valley.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
The following key helps in distinguishing all 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Αethionema">Αethionema</normalizedToken>
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Aethionema" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aethionema saxatile" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="saxatile">Aethionema saxatile</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
taxa found in Greece, Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T7679164" captionText="Table 1. Key to the subspecies of Aethionema saxatile found in Greece:" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/B017F4D075995F82A007E536384C812A" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" tableUuid="B017F4D075995F82A007E536384C812A">1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
Following a morphological and statistical approach, the close taxonomic proximity of subsp. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Constantinidis, Kougioumoutzis &amp; Kalpoutzakis" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="D. K. Pavlova" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Aethionema" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aethionema saxatile subsp. rhodopaeum" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="saxatile" subSpecies="rhodopaeum">Aethionema saxatile rhodopaeum</taxonomicName>
to the rest of the 
<taxonomicName genus="Ae." lsidName="Ae. saxatile" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="saxatile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Ae. saxatile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxa is unquestionable. However, a recent phylogenetic reconstruction places it away from 
<taxonomicName genus="Ae." lsidName="Ae. saxatile" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="saxatile">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Ae. saxatile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as it forms a monophyletic group with the annual Asiatic 
<taxonomicName genus="Ae." lsidName="Ae. syriacum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="syriacum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Ae. syriacum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Boiss.) Bornm. and the perennial 
<taxonomicName genus="Ae." lsidName="Ae. orbiculatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="orbiculatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Ae. orbiculatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Boiss.) Hayek, a local endemic of Mt. Athos, Greece (
<bibRefCitation author="Mohammadin, S." journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="1042 - 1054" refId="B7669001" refString="Mohammadin, S., Peterse, K., Kerke, S. J. van de, Chatrou, L. W., Doenmez, A. A., Mummenhoff, C., Pires, J. C., Edger, P. P., Al-Shehbaz, I. A., Schranz, M. E., 2017. Anatolian origins and diversification of Aethionema, the sister lineage of the core Brassicaceae. American Journal of Botany 104 (7): 1042 - 1054" title="Anatolian origins and diversification of Aethionema, the sister lineage of the core Brassicaceae" volume="104" year="2017">Mohammadin et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). A more detailed investigation of the whole group may be necessary in the future.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
subsp. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Constantinidis, Kougioumoutzis &amp; Kalpoutzakis" authorityYear="2017" baseAuthorityName="D. K. Pavlova" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Aethionema" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Aethionema saxatile subsp. rhodopaeum" order="Brassicales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="saxatile" subSpecies="rhodopaeum">Aethionema saxatile rhodopaeum</taxonomicName>
was previously known from a few, small populations in Bulgaria, where it has been assessed as Endangered, according to the IUCN Categories and Criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="Pavlova, D." journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="533 - 540" refId="B7669073" refString="Pavlova, D., 2007. A new species of Aethionema (Brassicaceae) from the Bulgarian flora. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 155: 533 - 540" title="A new species of Aethionema (Brassicaceae) from the Bulgarian flora" volume="155" year="2007">Pavlova 2007</bibRefCitation>
). The Greek population was found at a distance of 11 km south of the Greek-Bulgarian border, consists of a few dozens of plants and covers an area of just a few square metres (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 11" captionStartId="F7677586" captionText="Figure 11. Distribution map of Onosma kittanae, Aethionema saxatile subsp. rhodopaeum and Silene fetlerii in Greece and Bulgaria." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/656688" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">11</figureCitation>
). Its discovery expands the extent of occurrence, area of occupancy and population size of this rare plant; however, it remains an Endangered species at global level, according to Criteria [B1ab(ii iv) + 2ab(ii iv)]. At national level, the single Greek population fits the Category of Critically Endangered [B1ab(i ii iii iv) + 2ab(i ii iii iv)] (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN," journalOrPublisher="Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK: IUCN. iv + 32 pp" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668800" refString="IUCN, , 2012. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. Second edition. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK: IUCN. iv + 32pp" title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. Second edition" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
